vulnerability.name: USN-5332-2
vulnerability.description: USN-5332-1 fixed a vulnerability in Bind. This update provides the corresponding update for Ubuntu 14.04 ESM and Ubuntu 16.04 ESM.  Original advisory details:   Xiang Li, Baojun Liu, Chaoyi Lu, and Changgen Zou discovered that Bind  incorrectly handled certain bogus NS records when using forwarders. A  remote attacker could possibly use this issue to manipulate cache results.  (CVE-2021-25220)

statements.status_notes: Bind could be made to manipulate cache results. Available with Ubuntu Pro.
